  "conclusion": "The correctness-breaking Q/K TP-allreduce skip is slower and invalid. The normal quality path repeated near 39.5-39.6 output tok/s at p512/n512, 39.9-40.3 output tok/s at p512/n1024, and 40.9-41.1 output tok/s at p512/n1536. Setting max_model_len=4096 drops the same p512/n1536 request to 33.26 output tok/s at default memory; gpu_memory_utilization=0.95 recovers KV capacity and improves it to 36.62 tok/s. Setting max_model_len=8192 with gpu_memory_utilization=0.95 completes with 25,600 KV tokens but drops the same request to 33.31 output tok/s. Best rows and the capacity datapoints were submitted to LocalMaxxing."
